CAUTION
-------
 EPP will create files at the directory "eppout"
and subdirectories of the "eppout".
Do NOT put important files under the "eppout"
because they may be overwritten.
 In unix, making symbolic links under the "eppout" is also
dangerous.

 Please make backup of all important files
before execution of EPP.



JavaClass API
-------------
 EPP internally uses the package "JavaClass API" .
 JavaClass is a LGPL class library for byte-code engineering,
developed by Markus Dahm.
See src/JavaClassAPI/README for more details.
 To obtain full-set of class files, source files 
and documents of JavaClass, please visit the following URLs.

	http://www.inf.fu-berlin.de/~dahm/JavaClass/index.html
or
	http://staff.aist.go.jp/y-ichisugi/epp/JavaClass/JavaClass3.3.2.tar.gz


 EPP does NOT contain all class files provided by JavaClass.
 It only contains subset of class files required by EPP implementation.



